(3742, '_transient_wpum_addons_feed', 'a:7:{i:0;O:8:\"stdClass\":12:{s:2:\"id\";i:15797;s:4:\"slug\";s:13:\"custom-fields\";s:4:\"date\";i:1435795200;s:13:\"modified_date\";i:1530403200;s:4:\"link\";s:47:\"https://wpusermanager.com/addons/custom-fields/\";s:6:\"sticky\";b:0;s:5:\"title\";s:13:\"Custom Fields\";s:7:\"excerpt\";s:111:\"Create unlimited custom fields and groups for user profiles and registration form with a drag & drop interface.\";s:7:\"content\";s:2181:\"[vc_row top_padding=\"30\"][vc_column width=\"1/1\"][minti_headline type=\"h3\" size=\"fontsize-xl\" align=\"align-left\"]Create unlimited custom fields[/minti_headline][vc_column_text]The custom fields editor interface integrates with the existing WPUM fields editor. Field types are categorized as “Basic” and “Advanced”. Select a field type from the list to add it to the current group.[/vc_column_text][minti_imageslider ids=\"25508,25507\"][minti_headline type=\"h3\" size=\"fontsize-xl\" align=\"align-left\"]Categorize fields by groups[/minti_headline][vc_column_text]Create new field groups to separate fields based on their purpose. You can have as many groups as you want. On the front-end fields will be displayed by group. The edit account page on the front-end will also display a new tab for each field group.\r\n\r\nThe screenshots below show a new fields group called \"Custom fields\" for showcasing purposes, the account page then displays a new tab containing that field.[/vc_column_text][minti_image img=\"25509\" style=\"image_box_border\"][minti_image img=\"25510\" style=\"image_box_border\"][minti_headline type=\"h3\" size=\"fontsize-xl\" align=\"align-left\"]Fields administration on the backend[/minti_headline][vc_column_text]When new fields and groups are created, the same fields and groups will also be available on the backend. Site administrators will have access to all the information added by the users. If needed, administrators can also modify those information.[/vc_column_text][minti_image img=\"25511\" style=\"image_box_border\"][minti_headline type=\"h3\" size=\"fontsize-xl\" align=\"align-left\"]Custom Registration Fields[/minti_headline][vc_column_text]Customize the registration form and easily add new custom fields to create a personalized experience for your community.[/vc_column_text][minti_image img=\"25512\" style=\"image_box_border\"][minti_headline type=\"h3\" size=\"fontsize-xl\" align=\"align-left\"]Automatically display fields on the member\'s profile[/minti_headline][vc_column_text]Custom fields created through the addon, will automatically display within the user\'s profile on the frontend of your website, if you allow it.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]\";s:9:\"thumbnail\";s:92:\"https://wpusermanager.com/wp-content/uploads/edd/2015/07/custom_fields_groups-compressor.png\";s:10:\"categories\";a:0:{}s:4:\"tags\";a:0:{}}i:1;O:8:\"stdClass\":12:{s:2:\"id\";i:17978;s:4:\"slug\";s:12:\"social-login\";s:4:\"date\";i:1463184000;s:13:\"modified_date\";i:1530403200;s:4:\"link\";s:46:\"https://wpusermanager.com/addons/social-login/\";s:6:\"sticky\";b:0;s:5:\"title\";s:12:\"Social Login\";s:7:\"excerpt\";s:90:\"Allow your users to quickly login and register with their favorite social network account.\";s:7:\"content\";s:987:\"[vc_row top_padding=\"30\"][vc_column width=\"1/1\"][minti_headline type=\"h3\" size=\"fontsize-xl\" weight=\"fontweight-500\" align=\"align-left\"]Login &amp; Register via social networks[/minti_headline][vc_column_text]The social login addon allows users to easily register and login to your website using their social network accounts supported networks are Facebook, Twitter, Google, Instagram &amp; LinkedIn.\r\n\r\nThe add-on also automatically finds first name and last name of the user registering to the site and saves it within the account.[/vc_column_text][minti_headline type=\"h3\" size=\"fontsize-xl\" weight=\"fontweight-500\" align=\"align-left\"]Decide where to display the signup &amp; login buttons[/minti_headline][minti_image img=\"25486\" lightbox=\"1\" style=\"image_box_border\"][minti_headline type=\"h3\" size=\"fontsize-xl\" weight=\"fontweight-500\" align=\"align-left\"]Styled buttons with icons[/minti_headline][minti_image img=\"25487\" lightbox=\"1\" style=\"image_box_border\"][/vc_column][/vc_row]\";s:9:\"thumbnail\";s:84:\"https://wpusermanager.com/wp-content/uploads/edd/2018/06/social-login-compressor.png\";s:10:\"categories\";a:0:{}s:4:\"tags\";a:0:{}}i:2;O:8:\"stdClass\":12:{s:2:\"id\";i:17982;s:4:\"slug\";s:17:\"user-verification\";s:4:\"date\";i:1463184000;s:13:\"modified_date\";i:1530403200;s:4:\"link\";s:51:\"https://wpusermanager.com/addons/user-verification/\";s:6:\"sticky\";b:0;s:5:\"title\";s:17:\"User Verification\";s:7:\"excerpt\";s:101:\"Send a verification link via email upon registration or manually approve users before they can login.\";s:7:\"content\";s:1652:\"[vc_row top_padding=\"30\"][vc_column width=\"1/1\"][minti_headline type=\"h3\" size=\"fontsize-xl\" align=\"align-left\"]Registration moderation[/minti_headline][vc_column_text]Moderate registration and choose to approve or reject user’s registration through the \"Manage Signups\" page within your WordPress admin panel.[/vc_column_text][minti_image img=\"25478\" lightbox=\"1\" style=\"image_box_border\"][minti_headline type=\"h3\" size=\"fontsize-xl\" align=\"align-left\"]Automatic email verification[/minti_headline][vc_column_text]Choose wether to enable manual moderation of your members or to automatically approve members who verify their account via email by adding a new {verification_link} tag to your registration email.[/vc_column_text][minti_image img=\"25479\" lightbox=\"1\" style=\"image_box_border\"][minti_headline type=\"h3\" size=\"fontsize-xl\" align=\"align-left\"]Integrated dashboard widget[/minti_headline][vc_column_text]A dashboard widget will quickly tell you wether you have accounts pending verification.[/vc_column_text][minti_image img=\"25480\" lightbox=\"1\" style=\"image_box_border\"][minti_headline type=\"h3\" size=\"fontsize-xl\" align=\"align-left\"]Lockdown login when not verified[/minti_headline][vc_column_text]When a user is pending verification or approval, login with that account is locked down until verified. An error message appears on top of the login form.\r\n\r\nThe message automatically changes based on your verification method (manual or via email) In this example the text of the message refers to manual verification by an administrator.[/vc_column_text][minti_image img=\"25481\" lightbox=\"1\" style=\"image_box_border\"][/vc_column][/vc_row]\";s:9:\"thumbnail\";s:78:\"https://wpusermanager.com/wp-content/uploads/edd/2016/05/user_verification.png\";s:10:\"categories\";a:0:{}s:4:\"tags\";a:0:{}}i:3;O:8:\"stdClass\":12:{s:2:\"id\";i:15793;s:4:\"slug\";s:9:\"mailchimp\";s:4:\"date\";i:1435795200;s:13:\"modified_date\";i:1530403200;s:4:\"link\";s:43:\"https://wpusermanager.com/addons/mailchimp/\";s:6:\"sticky\";b:0;s:5:\"title\";s:9:\"MailChimp\";s:7:\"excerpt\";s:105:\"Subscribe your members to MailChimp lists easily during registration with this WP User Manager extension.\";s:7:\"content\";s:2801:\"[vc_row top_padding=\"40\" bottom_padding=\"0\"][vc_column width=\"1/1\"][minti_iconbox icon=\"fa-list-alt\"]Add users to one or more MailChimp lists when they register.[/minti_iconbox][minti_iconbox icon=\"fa-folder-open\"]Sync all your users with one or more lists from your MailChimp account.[/minti_iconbox][minti_iconbox icon=\"fa-desktop\"]Administrators can subscribe and unsubscribe users manually from the administration panel.[/minti_iconbox][minti_iconbox icon=\"fa-user-plus\"]Allow users to subscribe/unsubscribe from their account page.\r\n\r\n[/minti_iconbox][minti_headline type=\"h3\" size=\"fontsize-l\" weight=\"fontweight-700\" align=\"align-left\"]Easy configuration panel[/minti_headline][vc_column_text]Get your MailChimp integration up and running in a matter of minutes. Enable one or more lists to work with, sync your users and customize how your lists appear on your site.[/vc_column_text][minti_image img=\"25519\" lightbox=\"1\" align=\"center\" style=\"image_box_border\"][minti_headline type=\"h3\" size=\"fontsize-l\" weight=\"fontweight-700\" align=\"align-left\"]Sync Tool[/minti_headline][vc_column_text]The MailChimp addon comes with a Sync tool that lets you import all your users into a MailChimp list.Select the user role you wish to subscribe and a list, the tool will then start the import process.[/vc_column_text][minti_image img=\"17757\" lightbox=\"1\" align=\"center\" style=\"image_box_border\"][minti_headline type=\"h3\" size=\"fontsize-l\" weight=\"fontweight-700\" align=\"align-left\"]Working with lists[/minti_headline][vc_column_text]The add-on is capable of working with one or more lists at the same time. For example, your users can decide to signup to one or more lists. You can also choose to change the order with which they appear on your site and even add a custom description underneath each list.[/vc_column_text][minti_image img=\"25520\" lightbox=\"1\" align=\"center\" style=\"image_box_border\"][minti_headline type=\"h3\" size=\"fontsize-l\" weight=\"fontweight-700\" align=\"align-left\"]Registration &amp; Account Integration[/minti_headline][vc_column_text]Allow users to choose to which list they want to signup or automatically add users to a specific list. If needed you can also let your users subscribe and unsubscribe from lists directly from their account page.[/vc_column_text][minti_imageslider ids=\"25522,25524,25523\"][minti_headline type=\"h3\" size=\"fontsize-l\" weight=\"fontweight-700\" align=\"align-left\"]Custom fields integration with Merge fields on MailChimp[/minti_headline][vc_column_text]When combined with the <a href=\"https://wpusermanager.com/addons/custom-fields/\">custom fields addon</a>, WP User Manager can sync custom fields created with the add-on to merge fields created onto MailChimp.[/vc_column_text][minti_image img=\"25525\" style=\"image_box_border\"][/vc_column][/vc_row]\";s:9:\"thumbnail\";s:86:\"https://wpusermanager.com/wp-content/uploads/edd/2015/07/mailchimp_logo-compressor.png\";s:10:\"categories\";a:0:{}s:4:\"tags\";a:0:{}}i:4;O:8:\"stdClass\":12:{s:2:\"id\";i:15651;s:4:\"slug\";s:9:\"recaptcha\";s:4:\"date\";i:1436745600;s:13:\"modified_date\";i:1530403200;s:4:\"link\";s:43:\"https://wpusermanager.com/addons/recaptcha/\";s:6:\"sticky\";b:0;s:5:\"title\";s:16:\"Google reCaptcha\";s:7:\"excerpt\";s:108:\"State of the art spam & abuse protection for your website. Stop spam registrations on your website for free.\";s:7:\"content\";s:873:\"[vc_row top_padding=\"30\"][vc_column width=\"1/1\"][minti_headline type=\"h3\" size=\"fontsize-xl\" align=\"align-left\"]Add Google\'s reCAPTCHA to your login and registration forms.[/minti_headline][vc_column_text]reCAPTCHA is a free service to protect your website from spam and abuse. reCAPTCHA uses an advanced risk analysis engine and adaptive CAPTCHAs to keep automated software from engaging in abusive activities on your site. It does this while letting your valid users pass through with ease.[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]Add Google\'s reCAPTCHA noCAPTCHA to your website and protect your site from spam registrations and login.\r\n\r\nThis addon lets you choose which forms you wish to protect, you can decide to display the recaptcha field into the registration form, login forms and password recovery form, all with just a few clicks.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]\";s:9:\"thumbnail\";s:75:\"https://wpusermanager.com/wp-content/uploads/edd/2015/07/recaptcha_logo.png\";s:10:\"categories\";a:0:{}s:4:\"tags\";a:0:{}}i:5;O:8:\"stdClass\":12:{s:2:\"id\";i:25551;s:4:\"slug\";s:13:\"personal-data\";s:4:\"date\";i:1530144000;s:13:\"modified_date\";i:1530403200;s:4:\"link\";s:47:\"https://wpusermanager.com/addons/personal-data/\";s:6:\"sticky\";b:0;s:5:\"title\";s:13:\"Personal Data\";s:7:\"excerpt\";s:99:\"Allow the user to request an export/erasure of personal data from the account page of your website.\";s:7:\"content\";s:1383:\"[vc_row top_padding=\"30\"][vc_column width=\"1/1\"][minti_headline type=\"h3\" size=\"fontsize-xl\" align=\"align-left\"]Request personal data and request cancellation[/minti_headline][vc_column_text]Allow the user to request an export of personal data and request erasure of personal data <strong>from the account page</strong>.\r\n<h4>How it works</h4>\r\nOnce installed, a new tab called “Personal data” will be created within the <strong>user’s account page</strong>. The user will be requested to type his current password before requesting an export of data or before requesting erasure of personal data.\r\n\r\nUpon successful submission, requests will be logged under “Tools -&gt; Export personal data” and/or “Tools -&gt; Erase personal data” within your admin dashboard from where you can manage requests.\r\n\r\nThis add-on follows the way WordPress itself provides integration for privacy tools. The addon will evolve alongside WordPress when new privacy tools will be introduced.\r\n<h4>Email notifications</h4>\r\nWhen requesting an export or erasure of personal data, the user will receive a confirmation request email with a special link that once clicked, will mark the request as confirmed in your dashboard so that administrators can either send an export of data or erase personal data.[/vc_column_text][minti_image img=\"25553\" style=\"image_box_border\"][/vc_column][/vc_row]\";s:9:\"thumbnail\";s:73:\"https://wpusermanager.com/wp-content/uploads/edd/2018/06/privacyaddon.png\";s:10:\"categories\";a:0:{}s:4:\"tags\";a:0:{}}i:6;O:8:\"stdClass\":12:{s:2:\"id\";i:25531;s:4:\"slug\";s:14:\"delete-account\";s:4:\"date\";i:1530144000;s:13:\"modified_date\";i:1530403200;s:4:\"link\";s:48:\"https://wpusermanager.com/addons/delete-account/\";s:6:\"sticky\";b:0;s:5:\"title\";s:14:\"Delete Account\";s:7:\"excerpt\";s:92:\"Allows the user to delete their own profile from the frontend account page of your website. \";s:7:\"content\";s:727:\"[vc_row top_padding=\"30\"][vc_column width=\"1/1\"][minti_headline type=\"h3\" size=\"fontsize-xl\" align=\"align-left\"]Allow members to delete their account[/minti_headline][vc_column_text]Allows the user to delete their own profile from the <strong>frontend account page</strong>. After the account is deleted, the user can be redirected to a custom page.\r\n\r\nOnce installed, a new tab called “Delete account” will be created within the <strong>user’s account page</strong>. The user will be requested to type his current password before deleting the account and on submission a message asking for confirmation will be displayed.[/vc_column_text][minti_gallery ids=\"25532,25533,25534\" columns=\"3\" style=\"2\"][/vc_column][/vc_row]\";s:9:\"thumbnail\";s:74:\"https://wpusermanager.com/wp-content/uploads/edd/2018/06/accountdelete.png\";s:10:\"categories\";a:0:{}s:4:\"tags\";a:0:{}}}', 'no'),
